1
00:00:01,840 --> 00:00:07,140
Finally, you are going to see how to protect a PDF documents.

2
00:00:07,140 --> 00:00:10,940
What does it mean to protect a PDF document?

3
00:00:10,940 --> 00:00:17,340
PDF documents are digital replacements of paper‑based documents.

4
00:00:17,340 --> 00:00:23,340
You know that the paper‑based documents can be confidential sometimes.

5
00:00:23,340 --> 00:00:29,840
Similarly, it could be required to make digital documents confidential as well.

6
00:00:29,840 --> 00:00:35,840
PDF documents can be secured using passwords.

7
00:00:35,840 --> 00:00:39,740
It is possible to specify the permissions as to who

8
00:00:39,740 --> 00:00:43,040
can do what with a PDF document.

9
00:00:43,040 --> 00:00:49,740
According to the PDF specification, access permissions for a PDF document are

10
00:00:49,740 --> 00:00:55,340
print the document, modify the content of the document,

11
00:00:55,340 --> 00:01:02,940
copy or extract content of the document, add or modify annotations,

12
00:01:02,940 --> 00:01:09,010
fill in interactive form fields, extract text and graphics for

13
00:01:09,010 --> 00:01:13,980
accessibility to visually impaired people, assemble the

14
00:01:13,980 --> 00:01:19,440
document, print in degraded quality.

15
00:01:19,440 --> 00:01:24,810
There are two types of passwords that can be attached to a PDF document.

16
00:01:24,810 --> 00:01:27,520
They are the owner password,

17
00:01:27,520 --> 00:01:33,640
which enables to access a PDF with all eight permissions that you saw earlier,

18
00:01:33,640 --> 00:01:44,000
and they user password which enables to access with restricted permissions where you can specify what permissions you wish to give the user.

